FlowChart



Start

Display About Me section

Display Welcome Screen

Loop

Display Menu Options

Get User Input

Process User Input

If User Input is '1':

    Get List of Files

    Sort File Names in Ascending Order

    Display Sorted File Names

If User Input is '2':

    Get File Name to Add

    If File Already Exists:

        Display 'File Already Exists' Message

    Else:

        Create New File

        Display 'File Added Successfully' Message

        Write User Input to File

        Display 'Content Written to File Successfully' Message

If User Input is '3':

    Get File Name to Delete

    If File Exists:

        Delete File

        Display 'File Deleted Successfully' Message

    Else:

        Display 'File Does Not Exist' Message

If User Input is '4':

    Get File Name to Search

    If File Exists:

        Display 'File Found' Message

    Else:

        Display 'Error: File Not Found' Message

If User Input is '5':

    Display 'Goodbye' Message

    End Program

Get User Input to Continue or Quit

If User Input is 'q':

    Display 'Goodbye' Message

    End Program

If User Input is Not 'c':

    Display 'Invalid Input' Message


End Loop

End

